H0.text: When the egg is released from the ovary, what is left behind. Follicular Remnant

H1.text: When the egg is released from the ovary, what is left behind. Ovarian Cyst

H2.text: When the egg is released from the ovary, what is left behind. Corpus Hemorrhagicum

H3.text: When the egg is released from the ovary, what is left behind. Luteal

A4.text: The corpus luteum is the remains of the ovarian follicle that has released a mature ovum during a previous ovulation.

A5.text: The follicle first forms a corpus hemorrhagicum before it becomes a corpus luteum, but the term refers to the visible collection of blood, left after rupture of the follicle, that secretes progesterone.
